, "description": ["PHYSICIAN DUBBED 8RIGADIERGENERAL Trailing Ludicrous Precedent Village PusPaddier Will Be come Pretended Veteran of Gory Battlefields By HUGH W ROBERTS 0 Washington Bureau The AgeHerald 500 Davidson Building Washington March 8SpecialDr C E Sawyer of Marion O nominated fcy President Harding today to be a brig adier general will he Confirmed The democrats will not Interpose ob jection and will thus prove themselves to be bigger than the republicans who whined from the soul when President Wilson sought to elevate Dr Cary E Grayson to the rank of admiral This does not mean that every demo crat will vote for the confirmation of Hr Sawyer Individuals may vote against his confirmation But the great bulk or the party will support him and in so doing will declare the opinion that in making personal appointments the Presi dent should not be handicapped Republicans are prone to declare to day that the Grayson confirmation was the precedent on which President Hard ing based the nomination of Dr Saw yer But as Senator Harris of Georgia pointed out this afternoon the cases are not analagoos Dr Grayson has served two Presidents prior to his adoption by President Wilson and his elevation was in"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2022-09-26T03:53:26.109Z", "group": ["ndnp/au", "university-of-alabama-tuscaloosa-al-awardee"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/resource/sn85038485/1921-03-10/ed-1/?sp=7", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:au:batch_au_dean_ver01:data:sn85038485:00340583024:1921031001:0177/full/pct:6.25/0/default.jpg#h=441&w=309", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:ndnp:au:batch_au_dean_ver01:data:sn85038485:00340583024:1921031001:0177/full/pct:12.5/0/default.jpg#h=882&w=619", "https://tile.loc.gov/text-services/word-coordinates-service?segment=/service/ndnp/au/batch_au_dean_ver01/data/sn85038485/00340583024/1921031001/0177.xml&format=alto_xml"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"],